### Example 04: Handler Forms
### Server: http://localhost:3000

###############################
# Form 1: Simple Return Value
###############################

### Ping - Simple string
GET http://localhost:3000/ping

### Time - Map return
GET http://localhost:3000/time

###############################
# Form 2: Return with Error
###############################

### List Users - Might return error
GET http://localhost:3000/users

### Users Might Fail - Simulated error
GET http://localhost:3000/users-might-fail

###############################
# Form 3: Request Binding
###############################

### Create User - Valid
POST http://localhost:3000/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Charlie",
  "email": "charlie@example.com"
}

### Create User - Invalid (missing name)
POST http://localhost:3000/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Get User by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1

### Get User by ID - Not found
GET http://localhost:3000/users/999

###############################
# Form 4: Context + Request
###############################

### Get User Details - Check server logs for User-Agent
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1/details
User-Agent: MyCustomApp/1.0

###############################
# Form 5: Custom Response
###############################

### Custom Response - Success with headers (use -i to see headers)
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1/custom

### Custom Response - 404 error
GET http://localhost:3000/users/999/custom

###############################
# Comparison
###############################

### Compare Form 1
GET http://localhost:3000/compare/form1

### Compare Form 2
GET http://localhost:3000/compare/form2

### Compare Form 3 - With query param
GET http://localhost:3000/compare/form3?text=hello+world

### Compare Form 3 - Without param (uses default)
GET http://localhost:3000/compare/form3

### Compare Form 4 - Check server logs
GET http://localhost:3000/compare/form4
User-Agent: ComparisonTest/1.0
